<rdf:Description rdf:about="http://data.europa.eu/54i">
	<rdf:type rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Ontology"/>
	<dct:contributor>Thomas de Bodt</dct:contributor>
	<dct:creator>Eddy Vanderlinden</dct:creator>
	<dct:description xml:lang="en">The ECCF Core Ontology is part of the The European Commission Conceptual Framework (ECCF). It provides formal representation of the following story describing the European Commission:
		1. EC provides Services, which are of type Policy Formulation and Policy Execution.
		2. Policy Execution uses Financial Policy Instruments, Regulatory Policy Instruments, Transformations, and/or Assets.
		3. All Services are provided by Actors and realised by Transformations.
		4. Services and Policy Instruments are accessible through Channels. 
		5. Formulated policies are applicable for Territories.
		6. Assets are available at Locations.
		7. Services and Actors are motivated by Motivation.
		8. Actors are of type Persons and Organisations.
		9. Actors have Capabilities, can perform Transformations and use Services.
		10. All relations above are valid for periods of Time
		
	It can be reused by other Public Service organisations. </dct:description>
	<dct:creator>Ivo Velitchkov</dct:creator>
	<dct:title xml:lang="en">ECCF Core Ontology</dct:title>
	<owl:versionInfo xml:lang="en">1.18</owl:versionInfo>
	<rdfs:isDefinedBy rdf:resource="http://data.europa.eu/54i#"/>
</rdf:Description>

