	<rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">An individual member of class Temporal can have  one or two data-properties.
In the first case it refers to a point in time, in the second - to a period (or interval - see the difference in the comment of http://data.europa.eu/54i#hasPeriod), defined by periodStart and periodEnd.

All three properties have their domain declared as member of class Temporal. This means that, if one of these properties is used by members of other classes, that member will be inferred as member of the Temporal class. The purpose is to be able query all temporal information from that single class.

All three properties are declared as  functional. This means, each individual will have only one property of the kind.</rdfs:comment>
	<rdfs:isDefinedBy rdf:resource="http://data.europa.eu/54i#"/>
	<rdfs:label xml:lang="en">period start</rdfs:label>
	<skos:altLabel xml:lang="en">interval start</skos:altLabel>
</rdf:Description>

